OL,5,Csilence'
OL,7,FMenopause happens when periods stop
OL,8,Fbecause of lower hormone levels, and
OL,9,Fusually takes place between the ages
OL,10,Fof 45 and 55.
OL,12,FThe transitional phase, known as
OL,13,Fperimenopause, can last for years
OL,14,Fbefore a woman's final period.
OL,16,FNHS health checks are offered to
OL,17,Feligible people between the ages of 40
OL,18,Fto 74 every five years.
